news.title: Hyderabad: Land worth Rs 1,500 crore encroached, now demands regularisation
news.para: The CM reportedly told the CPI delegation that if the parcel was under Bhoodan land, the govt would consider their demand and if it’s a private land, the govt may not help. There has been a dispute over the land for several years.

news.title: Smartworks secures Rs 168 crore in funding round led by Keppel
news.para: According to a press release, the investment comes from a consortium of investors including Keppel Ltd., Ananta Capital Ventures Fund I, Plutus Capital, family trusts, and high-net-worth individuals.

news.title: Ambuja Cements board approves merger of Adani Cementation with company
news.para: The merger is totally based on share swapping and Adani Enterprises will get 8.7 million shares of Ambuja Cements, the consolidation of cement capacities within Adani Group is "to enhance operational efficiency" and strengthen Ambuja Cements' coastal footprint.

news.title: HC slams Maharashtra govt & SRA over delay in changing builder of redevelopment project
news.para: The State and the SRA cannot adopt such an approach to the matter when the occupants who vacated their premises in 2013 are neither close to getting their promised permanent accommodation nor any transit rent.

news.title: Aamir Khan buys apartment in Mumbai's Pali Hill for nearly Rs 10 crore
news.para: ​According to property registration documents accessed and analyzed by real estate consultant SquareYards(dot)com, Khan has executed the deed of transfer of a residential property in his name in Mumbai's Bandra suburb. The actor acquired this prestigious property for Rs 9.75 crore.

news.title: Country Garden gets trading resumption guidance from Hong Kong stock exchange
news.para: The stock exchange has asked the cash-strapped real estate firm to publish all its outstanding financial results along with any audit modifications, the company said in an exchange filing.

news.title: Home prices in Hong Kong fall 1.2% in May
news.para: Home prices dropped 1.2% last month from April after rising for two months in a row, official data showed on Wednesday. The monthly gain in April was revised to 0.5%.

news.title: Big US banks withstand Federal Reserve's commercial real estate shock scenario
news.para: As risks mount in the CRE space, investors were looking to the Fed's "stress tests" to assess how exposed America's lenders are at a time when pandemic-era work habits continue to empty office towers, sending vacancy rates past historic peaks to a record 20%.

news.title: Blackstone to buy Britain's Village Hotels
news.para: Blackstone said in a statement that funds managed by the firm had completed an acquisition of the hotel operator, which runs 33 mid-market hotels across regional cities and suburbs in Britain.

news.title: Sobha to launch rights issue on June 28 to raise up to Rs 2,000 crore
news.para: The Bengaluru-based company would issue 1,21,07,981 equity shares each on partly-paid basis for an amount up to Rs 2,000 crore.

news.title: Australia's Dexus to sell three assets for $255 million
news.para: Dexus said its 25% interest in 5 Martin Place was valued A$148.1 million. The stake is part of a 50% holding jointly held with Canada Pension Plan Investment Board, according to local media reports.

news.title: Concorde acquires 1.6-acre land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: This joint development will have a gross development value (GDV) of Rs 200 crore. The acquisition was facilitated by Colliers India.

news.title: First phase of Mumbai Metro 3 to be completed by December 2024
news.para: The first phase of Mumbai Metro 3, will run between SEEPZ (Santacruz Electronics Export Processing Zone) and Bandra Kurla Complex.

news.title: Goa: NGPDA gives time till July 25 to give feedback on draft Downtown Mapusa plan
news.para: The development of 11 lakh sqm under the Downtown Mapusa (Phase I) plan has been in the works since July 2015, when Laxmikant Parsekar was chief minister.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh and Telangana dispute over ownership of buildings in Hyderabad
news.para: Telangana and Andhra Pradesh dispute ownership of multiple buildings and assets in Hyderabad, with AP claiming rights over certain unlisted properties. The conflict highlights the complexities of dividing assets post the capital city transition.

news.title: Goa: Nearly 200 houses on Kadamba Plateau get water connections
news.para: However, the official sources said that though the new pipeline is being laid to connect the plateau to the state’s water supply network, the thousands of units in the residential complexes will receive water supply only after the individual houses are catered to first.

news.title: UltraTech Cement to acquire 23% stake for Rs 1,885 crore in India Cements
news.para: The Board of company at its meeting held on Thursday approved "making a financial investment to purchase up to 7.06 crores equity shares of India Cements Ltd," the filing said.

news.title: Ludhiana’s Smart City mission in further drag
news.para: It has been nine long years since the Smart City mission was launched, and Ludhiana was among the first 20 cities selected for this central programme.

news.title: Residents of Haware Citi in Thane up in arms against upcoming ready mix plants
news.para: Hyderabad-based Megha Engineering and Infrastructure Ltd is setting up two ready-mix cement (RMC) plants just a few hundred metres from their residential complex.

news.title: Land record management digitised in Tamil Nadu
news.para: Earlier the process was cumbersome for the buyer and seller, and required a compulsory visit to the taluk office for patta transfer, requesting measurement of land and for all land record based services.
